== 转移到北京 ==

在光绪二十三年（1897年）11月山东的[[巨野教案|两位德国神父被杀]]后，外国列强参与了一场“抢[[租借地|租借地]]”行为，威胁要将中国分裂为几个势力范围。<ref>{{cite book|author=Joseph W. Esherick|title=The Origins of the Boxer Uprising|url=https://archive.org/details/originsofboxerup00jose|url-access=registration|year=1987|location=Berkeley and Los Angeles|publisher=University of California Press|pages=[https://archive.org/details/originsofboxerup00jose/page/123 123–4]|isbn=0-520-06459-3}}</ref>为了保护都城对抗可能的攻击，慈禧于次年（1898年）夏将甘军调到北京。<ref name="Esherick 182">{{cite book|author=Joseph W. Esherick|title=The Origins of the Boxer Uprising|url=https://archive.org/details/originsofboxerup00jose|url-access=registration|year=1987|page=[https://archive.org/details/originsofboxerup00jose/page/182 182]}}</ref>因为她的宠臣荣禄与甘军统帅董福祥关系亲密，她欣赏甘军。<ref>{{cite book|author=Jonathan Lipman|title=Familiar Strangers|year=1997|page=157, note 120}}</ref>在去北京的路上，董福祥军攻击了[[保定|保定]]的基督教堂，毁了法国教堂。<ref name="Esherick 182"/><ref>[[:s:清史稿/卷443|《清史稿》卷四百四十三]]</ref>[[光绪帝|光绪帝]]支持的百日维新（1898年6月11日—9月21日）失败后，慈禧任命荣禄为[[兵部|兵部]]主事、[[军机大臣|军机大臣]]，负责节制、改组北洋各军。<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=wWvl9O4Gn1UC&pg=PA498|title=Some Did It for Civilisation, Some Did It for their Country: A Revised View of the Boxer War|author=Jane E. Elliott|year=2002|publisher=Chinese University Press|page=498|isbn=962-996-066-4|access-date=2017-03-02|archive-date=2021-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210208090506/https://books.google.com/books?id=wWvl9O4Gn1UC&pg=PA498|dead-url=no}}</ref>荣禄将董福祥的民兵组建为自己奏请设立的新军“武卫军”（北洋四大军甘军、武毅军、新建陆军、毅军的合编）的“后军”。<ref name=WZL/><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=wWvl9O4Gn1UC&pg=PA498|title=Some Did It for Civilisation, Some Did It for their Country|author=Jane E. Elliott|year=2002|page=498|publisher=Chinese University Press|isbn=978-962-996-066-7|access-date=2017-03-02|archive-date=2021-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210208090506/https://books.google.com/books?id=wWvl9O4Gn1UC&pg=PA498|dead-url=no}}</ref>董福祥是所有五个军（荣禄另外训练了一支中军）的统帅中，唯一不隐藏自己对外国人的敌意的。<ref>[[:s:清史稿/卷132|《清史稿》卷一百三十二]]</ref><ref name="Elliott 9">{{cite book|title=Some Did It for Civilisation, Some Did It for their Country|author=Jane E. Elliott|year=2002|page=9}}</ref>

甘军起初分别驻扎在涿州到正定一带。10月6日，清廷因甘军分别驻扎在正定一带不便操练，谕令除派何得彪六营赴芦台外，其余各营人马在11月7日由董福祥率领移驻京郊南苑。<ref name=WZL/>

北京居民和外国人都相似地害怕这支强横的穆斯林军队。<ref name="Elliott 9"/>二十四年（1898年）10月23日，据说“这些军队准备明天行动，彻底消灭北京所有的外国人，中国回到黄金年代。”<ref name="Esherick1988">{{cite book|author=Joseph W. Esherick|title=The Origins of the Boxer Uprising|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jVESdBSMasMC&pg=PA182|date=18 August 1988|publisher=University of California Press|isbn=978-0-520-90896-3|page=182}}</ref><ref name="HartFairbank1975">{{cite book|author1=Robert Hart|author2=John King Fairbank|author3=Katherine Frost Bruner|author4=Elizabeth MacLeod Matheson|author5=James Duncan Campbell|title=The I. G. in Peking: Letters of Robert Hart, Chinese Maritime Customs, 1868-1907|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=7ZybVIprRUMC&pg=PA1175|year=1975|publisher=Harvard University Press|isbn=978-0-674-44320-4|page=1175|access-date=2017-02-12|archive-date=2021-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210208090515/https://books.google.com/books?id=7ZybVIprRUMC&pg=PA1175|dead-url=no}}</ref>一些西方人将甘军描述为“10,000个伊斯兰暴民”，<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=2YleP1OP4HsC&pg=PA26|title=The Boxer Rebellion |author=Lynn E. Bodin |year=1979 |publisher=Osprey |page=26|isbn=0-85045-335-6 }}</ref>“一群约10,000人的乌合之众，其中大部分是伊斯兰教徒”，<ref>{{cite book|title=The rise of Chinese military power, 1895-1912|first1=Ralph L.|last1=Powell|year=1972|edition=illustrated, reprint|publisher=Kennikat Press|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=zs4mAQAAMAAJ|page=103|isbn=978-0-8046-1645-4}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author=Ralph L. Powell|title=Rise of the Chinese Military Power|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=akXWCgAAQBAJ&pg=PA103|date=8 December 2015|publisher=Princeton University Press|isbn=978-1-4008-7884-0|page=103|access-date=2017-02-12|archive-date=2021-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210208090541/https://books.google.com/books?id=akXWCgAAQBAJ&pg=PA103|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Papers on China, Volumes 3-4|others=Harvard University. East Asian Research Center, Harvard University. Committee on International and Regional Studies, Harvard University. East Asia Program, Harvard University. Center for East Asian Studies|year=1949|publisher=East Asian Research Center, Harvard University|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=nITjAAAAMAAJ|page=240|access-date=2017-02-12|archive-date=2021-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210208090535/https://books.google.com/books?id=nITjAAAAMAAJ|dead-url=no}}</ref>或“甘肃非正规军”，<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.wumunc.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Boxer-Rebellion.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=10 March 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160311033528/http://www.wumunc.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Boxer-Rebellion.pdf |archive-date=11 March 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref>其他人称之为“甚至为中国人所害怕的一万伊斯兰凶手”。<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=S8YtE0SIDq0C&pg=PA85 |title=The United States Marines in North China, 1894–1942 |author=Chester M. Biggs |year=2003 |publisher=McFarland |page=85 |isbn=0-7864-1488-X |access-date=2020-01-13 |archive-date=2021-02-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210208090545/https://books.google.com/books?id=S8YtE0SIDq0C&pg=PA85 |dead-url=no }}</ref>当年9月末和10月初，在甘军和外国人之间的几场小冲突使得首都紧张气氛上升。<ref name="Esherick 182"/>来自[[美国海军陆战队|美国海军陆战队]]的士兵们是从天津刚被召来保卫东交民巷免遭可能的袭击的新护卫军的一部分。<ref>Increase of legation guards: {{cite book|author=Joseph W. Esherick|title=The Origins of the Boxer Uprising|url=https://archive.org/details/originsofboxerup00jose|url-access=registration|year=1987|page=[https://archive.org/details/originsofboxerup00jose/page/182 182]}}</ref><ref>US Marine Corps: {{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=S8YtE0SIDq0C&pg=PA25 |title=The United States Marines in North China |author=Chester M. Biggs |year=2003 |page=25 |isbn=9780786480234 |access-date=2021-08-09 |archive-date=2022-01-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220109205115/https://books.google.com/books?id=S8YtE0SIDq0C&pg=PA25 |dead-url=no }}</ref>10月末，甘军准备杀死北京所有外国人的流言开始传播。<ref name="Esherick 182"/>为回应外国外交官们的最后通牒，慈禧令甘军转移到南苑。<ref>Official name Southern Park and explanation of the park's use: {{cite book|author=Susan Naquin|year=2000|title=Peking: Temples and City Life, 1400–1900|url=https://archive.org/details/pekingtemplescit0000naqu|location=Berkeley and Los Angeles|publisher=University of California Press|page=[https://archive.org/details/pekingtemplescit0000naqu/page/317 317]|isbn=0-520-21991-0}}</ref><ref>Reason for the Gansu Army's transfer: {{cite book|author=Joseph Esherick|year=1987|title=The Origins of the Boxer Uprising|url=https://archive.org/details/originsofboxerup00jose|url-access=registration|page=[https://archive.org/details/originsofboxerup00jose/page/182 182]}}</ref>截至1880年代，这片北京南的大片土地——它比墙内的城大数倍——已部分被改为农田，但便于在连接北京到天津的铁路附近驻扎。<ref>Farmland: {{cite book|author=Susan Naquin|year=2000|title=Peking|url=https://archive.org/details/pekingtemplescit0000naqu|page=[https://archive.org/details/pekingtemplescit0000naqu/page/317 317]}}</ref><ref>Railroad: see map in {{cite book|author=Diana Preston|year=2000|title=The Boxer Rebellion: The Dramatic Story of China's War on Foreigners that Shook the World in the Summer of 1900|url=https://archive.org/details/boxerrebelliondr0000pres|location=New York|publisher=Berkley Books|page=[https://archive.org/details/boxerrebelliondr0000pres/page/99 99]|isbn=0-425-18084-0}}</ref>甘军被卷入一场在一场剧院的混战。<ref name=Dowager>{{cite book|title=China Under the Empress Dowager|first1=J.O.P.|last1=Bland|first2=E.|last2=Backhouse|year=1910|url=https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.48303|page=360}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=China Under the Empress Dowager: Being the History of the Life and Times of Tzŭ Hsi|editor=John Otway Percy Bland |editor2=Edmund Backhouse |year=1911|publisher=J.B. Lippincott|url=https://archive.org/details/chinaunderempres01blan|page=[https://archive.org/details/chinaunderempres01blan/page/360 360]}}</ref>10月23日，两营甘军驻扎在芦沟桥附近，兵勇吴金福、赵新见等横站在[[丰台|丰台]]铁路段的铁路桥上，芦保铁路英国工程师哥士等喝令他们退让，他们不服，双方互相指骂，甘军士兵用石头打伤哥士和另一工程师头部，在场的英使馆人员甘伯乐也被微伤。哥士等人举枪射伤甘军两人。清廷令总理各国事务大臣[[胡燏棻|胡燏棻]]查办，英驻华公使[[窦纳乐|窦纳乐]]也函请总理衙门严办甘军士兵。26日，胡燏棻会晤窦纳乐，协商处理。窦纳乐等外国外交官们要求甘军撤走，因为他们威胁到了外国人的安全。<ref>{{cite news |date= 16 June 1900 |title=The Defence of Peking. Preparing to Resist Expedition  |url= http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article23837836 |newspaper= The West Australian |location=London |page=5|access-date= 1 April 2013}}</ref>最终，清廷棍责吴、赵二人，将甘军该部营官总兵衙尽先副将朱万荣和芦保铁路委员“交部议处”了结此事。原本甘军入京后，见到外国人就群起辱骂；此事后，各国公使愈发厌恶甘军，又怕其报复，上告请求不要调走甘军。平时使馆人员路过甘军驻地，策马疾驰而过，甘军从后面向他们扔石头，几乎出人命，从此使馆中人互相告诫，不敢走远。<ref name=HWT/>但清廷却对甘军大加赏赐。董福祥到南苑后，清廷派庆亲王[[奕劻|奕劻]]前往校阅，<ref name=HWT/>并在收到奕劻陈奏后下谕嘉奖董福祥治军有方，赏赐董福祥白玉翎管一支，白玉扳指一个，白玉柄小刀一把，由户部发赏银一万两给甘军兵勇，发小卷袍褂料二百卷由董福祥赏赐营哨各官。休息数日后，甘军离开南苑，驻[[蓟州|蓟州]]一带。二十五年（1899年）3月22日，清廷又下谕嘉奖董福祥。<ref name=WZL/>

董福祥所部甘军被编为武卫后军后，驻扎于丰润、玉田、蓟州一带。马福禄、马福祥所率回军马步各营驻扎永平府。<ref name=WZL/>

