== 义和团运动 ==
=== 义和团的兴起和回到墙内城区 ===
{{Blockquote|quote  = “二鬼子”一词被用于描述中国基督徒。在这些主房间之一的家庭中，告诉他们不要兴奋或尖叫。我刚聚集他们时，甘军中的19人闯入。他们的剑和衣服还滴着血，仿佛刚从屠宰场来。我上前见他们，礼貌地说：“我知道你们为什么而来：你们在寻找二鬼子。但我们中没有人‘吃了’外国宗教。你会看到我们在后屋有一个给灶神的祭坛。我们全家现在都在这里；你们要不要仔细查看这房间有没有藏着基督徒？”我的意思是暗示只要他们高兴，我们不会反抗他们的劫掠。我也叫了一个仆人备茶。我们的客人很愉快地接受这些建议，在几分钟的精力充沛的劫掠后他们回到了我的客房，其中一些坐下喝茶。其中一人说：‘你似乎是个可敬的人：可惜你住在这里的外国皈依者和间谍附近。’短暂停留后他们礼貌地感谢了我们，为闯入致歉，带着所得物品离开了。当时是大约下午2点。我们损失了价值大约$4,000的财物。不久后，火焰从我们邻居的后屋迸发出来，于是我做出决定搬家到城北的一个朋友室内。尽管有这些暴行，甚至聪明的人们仍然相信甘肃军人是中国的防御塔，能力足以驱逐任何数量的外国军队。我的一个朋友估计那个夏天北京有250,000人丧命。我曾如此攻击家庭中的拳民，以至于我自己的同情他们的亲戚称我为‘二毛子’，我的一个堂表亲担心拳民会杀我，一天诱导我去奶子府他们的一个神坛前磕头。直到今天我都在后悔自己屈膝的软弱。”
 |source = [[埃德蒙·巴恪思爵士，第二代从男爵|埃德蒙·巴恪思爵士，第二代从男爵]]和[[约翰·奥特维·坡尔西·布兰德|约翰·奥特维·坡尔西·布兰德]], 《北京宫廷回忆录（16到20世纪）》，第三幕，第一场。<ref>{{cite book|title=Annals & memoirs of the court of Peking: (from the 16th to the 20th century)|first1=Sir Edmund|last1=Backhouse|first2=John Otway Percy|last2=Bland|year=1914|publisher=W. Heinemann|url=https://archive.org/details/annalsmemoirsofc00back_2|page=[https://archive.org/details/annalsmemoirsofc00back_2/page/454 454]}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=The Atlantic Monthly, Volume 113|others=Carl Sandburg Collections (University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign Library)|year=1914|publisher=Atlantic Monthly Company|url=https://archive.org/details/atlanticmonthly06writgoog|page=[https://archive.org/details/atlanticmonthly06writgoog/page/n41 80]}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Annals & memoirs of the court of Peking: (from the 16th to the 20th century)|first1=Sir Edmund |last1=Backhouse|first2=John Otway Percy |last2=Bland|year=1914|publisher=W. Heinemann|url=https://archive.org/details/annalsmemoirsofc00back_2|page=[https://archive.org/details/annalsmemoirsofc00back_2/page/454 454]}}</ref>
}}

{{Blockquote|quote  = 这，因而，成为大部分盲目者的专利，将要发生一些惊人的事，一些超过任何其他曾被听闻的排外运动的事，因为此前从未有外国进口货用户和仅仅是外国人的朋友的人被标签为一种低于外国人自己的阶层。随着今天它变得黯淡，一种新鲜的兴奋浪潮淹没了城，几乎产生恐慌。董福祥野蛮的甘军的主体——他的全军——再次进京，迅速在北京外环[[天坛|天坛]]和[[先农坛|先农坛]]前的开阔地扎营。我很高兴地说，问题解决了。最终所有的使馆区颤抖了，紧急电报被送到英国海军请求不惜一切代价增援。|source = [[来自北京的有欠审慎的信函|来自北京的有欠审慎的信函]], 伯特兰·勒诺克斯·辛普森, pp. 36-7.<ref name="books.google.com"/><ref>{{cite book|title=Indiscreet Letters From Peking |first1=B L Putnam |last1= Weale |editor=John Otway Percy Bland |editor2=Edmund Backhouse|year=1907|publisher= Dodd Mead And Company |url=https://archive.org/stream/indiscreetletter008256mbp#page/n45/mode/2up |pages=36–7}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Indiscreet Letters from Peking: Being the Notes of an Eyewitness, which Set Forth in Some Detail, from Day to Day, the Real Story of the Siege and Sack of a Distressed Capital in 1900--the Year of Great Tribulation|editor-first=Bertram Lenox Putnam|editor-last=Weale|year=1909|publisher=Dodd, Mead|url=https://archive.org/details/indiscreetletter00wealiala|page=[https://archive.org/details/indiscreetletter00wealiala/page/29 29]}}</ref>
}}

光绪二十六年（1900年）1月5日，英國駐華公使[[窦纳乐|窦纳乐]]写信给[[英國外交及聯邦事務部|英國外交及聯邦事務部]]，内容是关于一场被称为“义和拳”的正在攻击[[山东|山东]]和[[南直隶省|南直隶省]]基督徒财产和中国信徒的运动。<ref>{{cite book|author=Paul A. Cohen|year=1997|title=History in Three Keys: The Boxers as Event, Experience, and Myth|url=https://archive.org/details/historyinthreeke00paul|url-access=registration|location=New York|publisher=Columbia University Press|page=[https://archive.org/details/historyinthreeke00paul/page/44 44]|isbn=0-231-10651-3}}</ref>当年最初的数月，“义和拳运动”在北京周围的北直隶地区戏剧性地扩张，拳民甚至开始在京城出现。<ref>Expansion of the Boxer movement: {{cite book|author=Paul A. Cohen|year=1997|title=History in Three Keys|url=https://archive.org/details/historyinthreeke00paul|url-access=registration|pages=[https://archive.org/details/historyinthreeke00paul/page/41 41–2]}}</ref><ref>Boxer arrival in Beijing: {{cite book|author=Joseph W. Esherick|year=1987|title=The Origins of the Boxer Uprising|url=https://archive.org/details/originsofboxerup00jose|url-access=registration|page=[https://archive.org/details/originsofboxerup00jose/page/290 290]}}</ref>5月末，反基督教的拳民产生了扩大化的排外改变，随着他们越来越有组织，他们开始攻打北京-[[保定|保定]]铁路，切断北京和天津之间的电报线路。<ref>{{cite book|author=Paul A. Cohen|year=1997|title=History in Three Keys|url=https://archive.org/details/historyinthreeke00paul|url-access=registration|page=[https://archive.org/details/historyinthreeke00paul/page/47 47]}}</ref>

清廷在剿灭、“安抚”或支持义和团之间犹豫。从5月27日到29日，慈禧在[[颐和园|颐和园]]与众人接见董福祥。<ref name="Xiang 207">{{cite book|author=Lanxin Xiang|year=2003|title=The Origins of the Boxer War: A Multinational Study|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=lAxresT12ogC&pg=PA207|location=London and New York|publisher=RoutledgeCurzon|page=207|isbn=0-7007-1563-0|access-date=2020-01-13|archive-date=2021-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210208090635/https://books.google.com/books?id=lAxresT12ogC&pg=PA207|dead-url=no}}.</ref>董福祥安慰她说自己能在必要的情况下消灭外国“蛮夷”，增加了太后对一旦战争不可避免的情况下中国驱逐外国人的能力的信心。<ref name="Xiang 207"/>同时，使馆护卫数目的增加——他们于5月31日到达北京——愈发引燃了北京及其周边乡村的排外情绪：第一次，拳民开始直接攻击外国人。<ref>{{cite book|author=Joseph W. Esherick|year=1987|title=The Origins of the Boxer Uprising|url=https://archive.org/details/originsofboxerup00jose|url-access=registration|page=[https://archive.org/details/originsofboxerup00jose/page/47 47]}}</ref>几个外国列强在[[大沽口|大沽口]]下派出战船，保护去天津和北京的道路。<ref>{{cite book|author=Paul A. Cohen|year=1997|title=History in Three Keys|url=https://archive.org/details/historyinthreeke00paul|url-access=registration|pages=[https://archive.org/details/historyinthreeke00paul/page/47 47–8]}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author=Joseph W. Esherick|year=1987|title=The Origins of the Boxer Uprising|url=https://archive.org/details/originsofboxerup00jose|url-access=registration|page=[https://archive.org/details/originsofboxerup00jose/page/287 287]}}</ref>慈禧太后调董福祥部甘军二十营共6786人驻南苑。[[端郡王|端郡王]][[载漪|载漪]]、刚毅又以京城空虚需要劲旅守卫为由，奏请调董福祥军入城。<ref name=WZL/>

6月9日，甘军的大部分将慈禧太后从颐和园护送回紫禁城；他们在城南天坛和先农坛前的空地扎营。甘军陆续入驻京城，屯扎于[[东华门|东华门]]、长安街一带，董福祥部驻东华门内甜水井。<ref name=WZL/>窦纳乐爵士担心最坏的情况，立即发电报请求[[爱德华·霍巴特·西摩尔|西摩尔海军中将]]从天津派援。6月10日，排外和支持义和团的载漪取代反义和团和更温和的[[庆亲王|庆亲王]]为[[总理各国事务衙门|总理各国事务衙门]]王大臣。总理各国事务衙门正是清政府用于与外国人沟通的机构。<ref name="Preston 70">{{cite book|author=Diana Preston|year=2000|title=The Boxer Rebellion|url=https://archive.org/details/boxerrebelliondr00dian|url-access=registration|page=[https://archive.org/details/boxerrebelliondr00dian/page/70 70]|isbn=9780802713612}}</ref>同日，电报线被永久切断。<ref name="Preston 69">{{cite book|author=Diana Preston|year=2000|title=The Boxer Rebellion|url=https://archive.org/details/boxerrebelliondr00dian|url-access=registration|page=[https://archive.org/details/boxerrebelliondr00dian/page/69 69]|isbn=9780802713612}}</ref>

=== 暗杀杉山彬 ===
{{Blockquote|quote= 6月11日发生了日本的书记生杉山彬被拳民和董福祥的甘军所杀一事。该书记生试图从永定门离开北京去见正在从天津赶来京城的西摩尔中将的援军，援军显然预期在次日到达北京。杉山乘坐一辆周身缠着表示主人至少是第二等级的宽红带子的马车。当他到永定门时，被一些正在把守它的董福祥部卒搭讪。似乎那天端郡王已下达了密令，不许任何外国人出入城。杉山因此被拦下并被问及身份。杉山告诉他们，他是日本使馆区的一员。“你是日本外交官吗？”“不，我只是使馆区的一位书记生。”“那么，你这样一个士官有什么权利乘坐这样一辆高官的车？”于是他们把他从马车上拉出来，开始围攻这个不幸的书记生。杉山随后请求被带到董福祥将军面前。“什么！你和我们大帅说话！为什么，你太渺小了，没有这样的荣誉！”最后，一个身着红色纽扣的甘肃军官出现，杉山向他求助。但这位暴徒没有这么做，仅仅下令砍掉这位日本书记生的头祭旗，且就在门前，“因为他试图冲出北京。”杉山是第一个在北京内被杀的外国人。
北京的大量人口被这些嗜血的事件极大地惊吓到了，他们都期望太后对这位属于友邦又是大使馆成员的书记员的被杀表示出一定的不赞同；但满族人得知此凶杀后，都表现出欢欣。最后对这场发生于最高地区的卑鄙凶杀的官方批准公章是端郡王盖的，当他次早遇到董福祥将军后，猛击后者的背部，竖起右手大拇指说“好！”竖起这根手指表示被评价的人为“一流的英雄。”
 |source = China and the Boxers: A short history of the Boxer outbreak, with two chapters on the sufferings of missionaries and a closing one on the outlook, ''Zephaniah Charles Beals'', pp. 73-5.<ref>{{cite book|title=China and the Boxers: A short history of the Boxer outbreak, with two chapters on the sufferings of missionaries and a closing one on the outlook|first=Zephaniah Charles|last=Beals|year=1901|publisher=M.E. Munson|url=https://archive.org/details/cu31924023150356|page=[https://archive.org/details/cu31924023150356/page/n76 73]}}</ref>
}}

{{Blockquote|quote=6月11日——此日，已留在南苑的董将军军队的一般主体进入永定门。这是这座中国城市南面的中央门。他们遇到了一位书记员，杉山，来自日本使馆区，正要离开北京去见来到北京的外国军队。董将军的军队问他他是谁。他回答他是日本使馆区的一位官方书记员。士兵们反对，如果你是一位官方书记员，为什么你用围绕着红带子的马车。他们抓住他的耳朵，让他下马车。这个书记员知道这不是动用理智的时间。他用说服的口吻说“请允许我见你们的大帅，我会向他道歉。”士兵们说：“不需要。”“然后，”他说，“我稍后会邀请你们的大帅去我的使馆区，我的外交官会道歉。”这些持剑的军官然后切开了他的腹部，杀死了他。日本外交官听闻后，请求获准带尸体回城安葬。好久后，才获准。端郡王随后见了董将军，伸出大拇指说：“你真是英雄。”|source =  The Boxer Rising: A History of the Boxer Trouble in China, pp. 59-60.<ref>{{cite book|title=The Boxer Rising: A History of the Boxer Trouble in China|edition=2, reprint|year=1901|publisher=Shanghai Mercury|url=https://archive.org/details/cu31924023150737|page=[https://archive.org/details/cu31924023150737/page/n80 59]}}</ref> [[The_Boxer_Rising:_A_History_of_the_Boxer_Trouble_in_China._Reprinted_from_the_"Shanghai_Mercury."|The Boxer Rising: A History of the Boxer Trouble in China. Reprinted from the "Shanghai Mercury."]], pp. 46-7.<ref>{{cite book|title=The Boxer Rising: A History of the Boxer Trouble in China. Reprinted from the "Shanghai Mercury."|edition=reprint|year=1900|publisher=Shanghai mercury, limited|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=n88WAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA46|page=46}}</ref>
}}

6月11日早晨，英军派出一支大马车队迎接[[西摩尔远征|西摩尔远征]]。队列安全通过了城墙内甘军占领的地区，很快到了北京南的[[马家堡|马家堡]]<ref name="Preston2000">{{cite book|author=Diana Preston|title=The Boxer Rebellion: The Dramatic Story of China's War on Foreigners That Shook the World in the Summer of 1900|url=https://archive.org/details/boxerrebelliondr00dian|url-access=registration|date=1 June 2000|publisher=Walker|isbn=978-0-8027-1361-2|page=[https://archive.org/details/boxerrebelliondr00dian/page/62 62]}}</ref>火车站，援军预期很快就要到达这里。<ref name="Preston 70"/>但援军没有到，这些马车只能回到使馆区。<ref name="Preston 70"/>一支规模稍小的意大利代表团在少数步兵护卫下侥幸躲过正列队封堵北京主要的南门永定门的董福祥的士兵，也安全返回。<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=lAxresT12ogC|title=义和团战争的起源:跨国研究|author=相蓝欣|year=2003|page=252|isbn=9780700715633|access-date=2017-02-18|archive-date=2017-03-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170323132421/https://books.google.com/books?id=lAxresT12ogC|dead-url=no}}</ref>

当天下午，日本使馆区派无护卫的书记生杉山彬去车站迎接日军。杉山彬穿着正式西装和一顶[[圆顶硬礼帽|圆顶硬礼帽]]，成为了一个引人注目的目标。<ref name="Preston 71">{{cite book|author=Diana Preston|year=2000|title=The Boxer Rebellion|url=https://archive.org/details/boxerrebelliondr00dian|url-access=registration|page=[https://archive.org/details/boxerrebelliondr00dian/page/71 71]|isbn=9780802713612}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=The Cambridge History of China|editor1-first=John King|editor1-last=Fairbank|editor2-first=Denis Crispin|editor2-last=Twitchett|year=1980|publisher=Cambridge University Press|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=pEfWaxPhdnIC&pg=PA121|page=121|isbn=0521220297|access-date=2017-02-21|archive-date=2021-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210208090724/https://books.google.com/books?id=pEfWaxPhdnIC&pg=PA121|dead-url=no}}</ref>甘肃穆斯林军在永定门附近把他从马车上抓下来，把他砍成碎片，斩了他的头，将他被肢解的尸体和被切断的头和生殖器丢在街上。<ref>{{cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/warriorsofrising00edge|url-access=registration|title=Warriors of the rising sun: a history of the Japanese military|author=Robert B. Edgerton|year=1997|publisher=W. W. Norton & Company|page=[https://archive.org/details/warriorsofrising00edge/page/70 70]|isbn=0-393-04085-2}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=yo0CAAAAMAAJ|title=The siege of the Peking legations: a diary|author1=Lancelot Giles|author2=Leslie Ronald Marchant|year=1970|publisher=University of Western Australia Press|page=181|isbn=9780855640415|access-date=2017-02-21|archive-date=2021-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210208090659/https://books.google.com/books?id=yo0CAAAAMAAJ|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=A forgotten conference: the negotiations at Peking, 1900-1901|first=John S.|last=Kelly|year=1963|publisher=Librairie Droz|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jXEIcDWjad4C&pg=PA31|page=31|isbn=2600039996}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=A Dance with the Dragon: The Vanished World of Peking's Foreign Colony|first=Julia|last=Boyd|edition=illustrated|year=2012|publisher=I.B.Tauris|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=5vFLjPAq-p0C&pg=PA4|page=4|isbn=978-1780760520}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Imperial Designs: Italians in China 1900–1947|series=The Fairleigh Dickinson University Press Series in Italian Studies|first=Shirley Ann|last=Smith|year=2012|publisher=Lexington Books|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=zNs51BGkrfQC&pg=PA18|page=18|isbn=978-1611475029}}</ref>《[[泰晤士报|泰晤士报]]》的北京通讯员[[莫理循|莫理循]]称他们还挖出他的心送给了董福祥。<ref name="Preston 71"/><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=5K9BN96p1hcC&pg=PA52|title=William Scott Ament and the Boxer Rebellion: heroism, hubris and the "ideal missionary"|author=Larry Clinton Thompson|year=2009|publisher=McFarland|page=52|isbn=978-0-7864-4008-5|access-date=2017-02-21|archive-date=2021-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210208090750/https://books.google.com/books?id=5K9BN96p1hcC&pg=PA52|dead-url=no}}</ref>日本使馆区在总理衙门提出了正式抗议，总理衙门表达了歉意，解释杉山彬是被“盗匪”所杀的。<ref>{{cite book|title=义和团战争的起源:跨国研究|author=相蓝欣|year=2003|page=253}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=iOahF7fBu1EC&pg=PA53|title=Peking 1900: The Boxer Rebellion|first= Peter |last=Harrington| year = 2013|edition=illustrated |publisher=Osprey Publishing|page=53|isbn=978-1472803047}}</ref>

慈禧太后责怪董福祥，想派员查办，董福祥坚称无此事，说：“就算真的有，斩了奴才无妨，如果斩了甘军一人，定然生变。”<ref name=HWT/>清廷就暂未追究。<ref name=WZL/>

=== 战斗 ===
在16日起连续四天的御前会议上，载漪认为董福祥对抗外夷应当无敌，慈禧太后也认为可以依靠董福祥抵抗洋人。<ref name=WZL/>

董福祥极度排外，对慈禧和拳民给予全力支持。董将军派他的穆斯林军队加入拳民攻打北京的外国人。他们不间断地攻打[[东交民巷|使馆区]]。他们也以不容[[鸦片|鸦片]]贸易闻名。一位日本书记生杉山彬和几位西方人被甘军所杀。<ref name="anu">{{cite web|url=http://dspace.anu.edu.au/handle/1885/43694|title=ANU - Digital Collections: Kansu Soldiers (Tung Fu Hsiang's)|publisher=dspace.anu.edu.au|access-date=2014-09-25|archive-date=2009-10-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091014184207/http://dspace.anu.edu.au/handle/1885/43694|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="anu2">{{cite web|url=http://dspace.anu.edu.au/bitstream/1885/43694/3/2762167112002_1.59.1.jpg|title=Kansu Braves|publisher=dspace.anu.edu.au|access-date=2014-09-25}}</ref><ref name="Clark">{{cite web|url=http://www.russojapanesewar.com/boxers.html|title=The Boxer Uprising 1899–1900.|last=Clark|first=Kenneth G.|website=www.russojapanesewar.com|access-date=2010-06-28|archive-date=2021-02-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210225035030/http://www.russojapanesewar.com/boxers.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

在北京的德国公使[[克林德|克林德]]轻易因怀疑一个中国公民是拳民而将其杀死。<ref>{{cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/warriorsofrising00edge|url-access=registration|title=Warriors of the Rising Sun: a History of the Japanese Military|author=Robert B. Edgerton|year=1997|publisher=W. W. Norton & Company|page=[https://archive.org/details/warriorsofrising00edge/page/70 70]|isbn=0-393-04085-2}}</ref>作为回应，拳民和数千中国穆斯林甘军继续对西方人的暴力骚乱。<ref>{{cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/dragonladylifean00seag|url-access=registration|title=Dragon Lady: The Life and Legend of the Last Empress of China|author1=Sterling Seagrave |author2=Peggy Seagrave |year=1992|publisher=Knopf|page=[https://archive.org/details/dragonladylifean00seag/page/320 320]|isbn=9780679402305}}</ref>

他们由5,000装备了最先进的连发步枪的骑兵组成。<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=WmAuAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA452-IA1|title=China in Convulsion, Volume 2|first=Arthur Henderson|last=Smith|year=1901|publisher=F. H. Revell Co.|location=Albany, N. Y.|page=441|access-date=2017-02-28|archive-date=2021-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210208090829/https://books.google.com/books?id=WmAuAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA452-IA1|dead-url=no}}</ref>其中一些是骑马前来的。<ref>{{cite book|title=The Boxer Rebellion|first=Richard|last=O'Connor|year=1973|edition=illustrated, reprint|publisher=Hale|isbn=0709147805|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LYVxAAAAMAAJ|page=163|access-date=2020-01-13|archive-date=2021-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210208090752/https://books.google.com/books?id=LYVxAAAAMAAJ|dead-url=no}}</ref>

